	<h1 class="uppercase-text">How to start?</h1>
	<br />
	<p><span class="blue-text"><strong>Be ready to get creative.</strong></span> You need to be good or you have to have someone with you at designing to surprise your customers with unique artwork.</p>
	<p><span class="blue-text"><strong>Be ready to reach your first customers.</strong></span> They can be organizations (schools, high schools, companies activating in certain industries), privates (friends, families, colleagues) or occasions (business meeting, birthdays, business gifts etc.).</p>
	<p><span class="blue-text"><strong>Be ready to make a study about what kind of products you will provide to the customers.</strong></span> They can range from electronic gadgets (phone covers, cable chargers, power banks etc.), PVC cards (unique business cards, FDR cards, cash card, membership cards etc.), various promotional items (pens, lighters, key chains etc.), office stationeries (pen boxes and pen holders, rulers, mouse pads etc.) to medals and trophies (metal, crystal or acrylic medals etc.), interior decorations (photo frames printed on wood, stone, metal, table displays, wedding pictures, wood coasters etc.), toys / play around (ping pong balls, puzzles, Lego bricks etc.) and many more.</p>
	<p><span class="blue-text"><strong>Be ready with your first samples to make your business known to the customers.</strong></span> No matter the customer that will be reached nor the product you will provide, you should be armed with samples to attract your customers (internet virtual demo, customer meetings or real products delivery).</p>
